args: Let's go, boys! Throw that Captain Karina\nand her crew into the sea!
That's it! I am NOT going to let these\nsoggy sods ruin my opera!
Yar, maybe we need to stop worryin'\nabout the opera, Cap'n?
Those pirates be ready for a scrap,\nso they be!
How dare ye do what ye did to us!\nWe'll have our revenge!
Ready yerselves for a... Huh?\nYar, their ship look passin' strange.
And there be a crowd on the beach.\nYar, what're ye sods gawkin' at!\nThis ain't no show!
You're almost right—this is no\nORDINARY show...
This is the OPERA—the greatest of the\narts, where we thrill our audience with\nsong AND drama!

We're off-book again, but that's just how
these things go. New finale, everyone!
It's time for a showdown with this band
of ugly mugs!
Ye dirty sea dogs! Ye stain our eyes!\nBut if a fight ye be seekin',\nwe'll gladly oblige! ♪

You may be a pirate
with wiles most sadistic,
But if you think you'll defeat me,
that's a bit optimistic! ♪
Thank heavens it's just part of the show!
(Excellent! The audience is calming down.\nNow to dash these sods on the shoals!)
This is the Karina Pirates' first battle,\nand I shall mark the day with a victory!
What are ye jabbering on about, Karina?!\nDo ye seek to play us for fools?!
Oh, not at all. I'm totally serious.\nBecause letting you walk free,\nwould be most deleterious! ♪
Yar, I got no idea what them big words\nmean, but she be keepin' the opera goin'!
Hold on, Cap'n! Hold on a sec!\nI be runnin' to your side\nwhat to give them dogs heck!
What in the name'a all the hells\ndo they be singin' and fightin' for?!
If ye need brawn, then I be your man!\nI'll stuff this cur into the garbage can! ♪
Count on me too! Count on me now!\nIf ye need a butt-whuppin',\nthen I'll show ye how! ♪
WHAT THE HELL BE GOIN' ON?!

We're the Karina Pirates!
The pirates of fame!
And we're gonna make sure
you remember our name! ♪
Yar, he be fallin' into the deep!
Ye fool! Don't ye see?!\nNow you're open to me! ♪
Ye may have beaten us today,\nbut there always be tomorrow!
We're not afraid! We've courage to spare!\nAnd if you want a fight,\nwe'll always be there! ♪
The pirate lady is soooo cool!
Gar, listen to that applause...\nThe cap'n did it, so she did!
They're not clapping for me,\nyou daft dogs...
Yar, they be complimentin' me?\nI can't be believin' it... *sniff*
*sniff* N-now I be moved, by gar!
You played your parts well, everyone.\nTime to line up and bow to the crowd.
To the actors, the orchestra, and the crew,\nthank you for all of your hard work.
Now...let's get this cast party GOING!
Gahar har har! What a day!
Me blood ran cold when ye tumbled\ninto the briney blue, so it did!
And me timbers shivered when those\nother pirates dogs appeared!
Yes, but that made for the perfect\nfinale. Lucky thing, that.
In fact, I think we're going to have a big\nfight at the end of EVERY performance!
And hey, that's how it went down back\nin the day too. You fell into the water\nand everyone found out you can't swim.
Then you attacked me when I saved you.\nI get you were embarrassed and all, but\nyou still ended up losing to me.
Yar, no need to open old wounds...
All right, we'll table that for now. Still,\nchanging the script a tad bit with every\nperformance sounds like great fun!
After all, this is an opera that's free\nand unbound by anything at all!
It should be fun not only for the audience,\nbut also for the performers!
All right, sea dogs! When the sun rises,\nwe're setting off for the next island!
The next morning, Karina and her crew\nset sail into the great, wide sea.
Yar, that be a fine tailwind...\nHoist the sail, lads! We're off!
We're Karina's Pirate Opera Troupe!\nWe steal boredom and deliver freedom,\nand no one ever stands in our way!
